{"type":"message","id":"44e82bd2","parentId":"20780458","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:54:44.480Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says `xurl auth apps add xai-prod` failed because it already exists. They need to either update the existing app's credentials or use a different approach to update the credentials for an existing app.\n\nLet me check what commands xurl has for updating app credentials. From the SKILL.md I didn't see an \"update\" command, but there might be one. Let me think...\n\nLooking at the SKILL.md:\n- `xurl auth apps list` - list apps\n- `xurl auth apps remove NAME` - remove app\n\nThere's no explicit \"update\" command mentioned. But the command structure is `xurl auth apps add NAME --client-id XXX --client-secret YYY`. \n \nSince the app already exists, I could remove it first and then re-add it with the correct credentials. Or I could look for an update flag on the add command itself. The safest bet is probably to remove the existing app and register it fresh with the right credentials, though I should verify that actually works first.\n","thinkingSignature":"f7d51bd9a84c412c626a807428c0cd27f18f76daacb67397afb939210fb8223b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNo worries Bobby! Since it already exists, you have two options:\n\n---\n\n## Option 1: Remove and Re-add (Cleanest)\n\n```bash\n# Remove the old one\nxurl auth apps remove xai-prod\n\n# Re-add with correct credentials\nxurl auth apps add xai-prod --client-id YOUR_NEW_CLIENT_ID --client-secret YOUR_NEW_CLIENT_SECRET\n```\n\nThen verify:\n```bash\nxurl auth status\n```\n\n---\n\n## Option 2: Check What App Exists\n\nFirst, let's see what's already there:\n```bash\nxurl auth apps list\n```\n\nIf you see `xai-prod` is already set up with the right permissions/scopes, you might just need to re-run the OAuth flow:\n\n```bash\nxurl auth oauth2\n```\n\n---\n\n## Quick Tip\n\nIf the existing app credentials are wrong/outdated, **Option 1 (remove + re-add)** is the cleanest fix.\n\nGo grab your new client ID and secret from the XAI portal, then run those commands in your terminal. Let me know what `xurl auth apps list` shows if you get stuck! 🔑"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35695,"output":445,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36268,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777690472718,"responseId":"06449a6ad28fe833050ca8aaff1c3ae3"}}
