{"type":"message","id":"4a66c893","parentId":"9f34029c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:57:10.074Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is having trouble with the xurl auth oauth2 flow. Let me help them debug. Common issues:\n\n1. The OAuth redirect might have failed\n2. The client ID/secret might be wrong\n3. The app might not have the right OAuth settings in the XAI portal\n4. The scopes might need to be configured\n\nLet me think about what could cause \"something went wrong\":\n\n1. If the client ID/secret are wrong - it would fail at authentication\n2. If the OAuth app in the XAI portal doesn't have the right redirect URI configured - it might fail\n3. The user might need to check the XAI portal to see what's configured for their app\n\nLet me ask them to check a few things:\n1. What does `xurl auth apps list` show?\n2. Did they configure the OAuth app correctly in the XAI developer portal?\n3. Is the redirect URI set correctly?\n\nThe SKILL.md says the user must register the app manually. Let me help them debug this.\n","thinkingSignature":"f565ed2e49bf0025ce8e1811c5dcd9344aa10d8b6be47c1843a3ef691c46a0c8"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNo stress Bobby, let's debug this. A few things to check:\n\n---\n\n## Check 1: What Apps Are Registered?\n\n```bash\nxurl auth apps list\n```\n\nWhat does it show?\n\n---\n\n## Check 2: OAuth App Setup in XAI Portal\n\nThe issue might be on the XAI side. Go to your XAI Developer Portal and check:\n\n1. **OAuth App settings** — is the redirect URI configured?\n   - Should be: `http://localhost`\n   \n2. **Permissions/Scopes** — does the app have these enabled?\n   - `tweet.read`\n   - `tweet.write`\n   - `offline.access`\n   - `users.read`\n   - `follows.read`\n\n3. **Client ID/Secret** — copy them EXACTLY as shown in the portal (watch for spaces, hidden chars)\n\n---\n\n## Check 3: Try Re-Registering\n\nIf the old app is broken, start fresh:\n\n```bash\n# Remove existing\nxurl auth apps remove xai-prod\n\n# Re-add with EXACT credentials from portal\nxurl auth apps add xai-prod --client-id \"YOUR_ACTUAL_CLIENT_ID\" --client-secret \"YOUR_ACTUAL_CLIENT_SECRET\"\n```\n\nMake sure you include the quotes around the values in case there are special characters.\n\n---\n\n## Check 4: Try With User Flag\n\nSometimes adding a username helps:\n```bash\nxurl auth oauth2\n```\n\nIf it still fails, try:\n```bash\nxurl auth oauth2 --username bobbygalletta\n```\n(replace with your actual X username)\n\n---\n\n## Share What You See\n\nRun these and paste what you get:\n```bash\nxurl auth apps list\nxurl auth status\n```\n\nI'll help you figure out where it's breaking. The \"something went wrong\" is likely either:\n\n- Wrong client ID/secret\n- Missing OAuth settings in the portal\n- Redirect URI misconfigured\n\nLet's get this sorted! 🔧"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35759,"output":621,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36700,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777690607204,"responseId":"06449aefbdee8e21515b383b0c3ecdd4"}}
