{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"3579\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-05-01 23:05 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"8d84d5e2","parentId":"de1cc0bf","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:05:56.107Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"7ed6d1e4","parentId":"8d84d5e2","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:06:14.933Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the status shows:\n1. `xai-prod` is registered with a client_id starting with \"WDNldnBy...\"\n2. oauth2: (none) - meaning no OAuth token yet\n3. The /2/users/me returned 401 Unauthorized\n\nThis means the credentials for xai-prod don't seem to be valid (or they're placeholder/test credentials). The client_id starting with \"WDNldnBy...\" looks like a real format but might be from the old x-app setup.\n\nBobby needs to:\n1. Get real OAuth credentials from the XAI Developer Portal (not x.com apps, but the XAI API portal)\n\n\n2. Re-register with the correct credentials\n\nThe \"YOUR_CLI...\" in my-app and \"WDNldnBy...\" in xai-prod both look suspicious—these might be legacy Twitter app credentials rather than actual XAI OAuth credentials, so Bobby should pull fresh credentials from the XAI Developer Portal at https://api.x.com/\n\napp to replace these.\n","thinkingSignature":"18c6a484475710cb3fef32cccd10ff35df7c0217ae815cf04a7ec7510c0c0c3c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGot it — `oauth2: (none)` means we have **no authentication token yet**. The 401 is because the app is registered but not authorized.\n\n---\n\n## What's Happening\n\n`xai-prod` shows a partial client_id (`WDNldnBy...`) — that's likely the OLD Twitter/X app credentials, not the current XAI ones. The OAuth flow failed because those credentials are wrong or outdated.\n\n---\n\n## You Need Fresh XAI Credentials\n\nGo to: **https://api.x.com/** (XAI Developer Portal)\n\n1. Sign in\n2. Go to your **OAuth App settings**\n3. Grab the **Client ID** and **Client Secret** (the current XAI ones, not old Twitter dev credentials)\n\n---\n\n## Then Re-register\n\n```bash\n# Remove the old broken one\nxurl auth apps remove xai-prod\n\n# Add with FRESH credentials from the portal\nxurl auth apps add xai-prod --client-id \"PASTE_REAL_CLIENT_ID_HERE\" --client-secret \"PASTE_REAL_CLIENT_SECRET_HERE\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Important Notes\n\n- **Don't use quotes if your ID/secret has no spaces** — just paste them directly\n- Make sure you copy the FULL client ID and secret (they're long)\n- The redirect URI should already be correct (`http://localhost:8080/callback`)\n\n---\n\n## After Adding Credentials\n\n```bash\n# Set as default\nxurl auth default xai-prod\n\n# Run OAuth flow\nxurl auth oauth2\n```\n\nThis should open a browser window. If it fails again, tell me exactly what error you see.\n\n---\n\n**Go get those fresh XAI credentials from the portal and try again!** 🔑"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":36700,"output":564,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37584,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777691156107,"responseId":"06449d14671ab6e03bb1ccf7f4963dc8"}}
