{"type":"message","id":"1c71e4e5","parentId":"ea78f803","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:43:14.480Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to check Activity Monitor for things that might be slowing down his MacBook Air. Let me check what's running - this is a diagnostic task. I should use exec to run some commands that give a view of what's consuming resources.\n\nFor a MacBook Air M2 8GB, the usual suspects are:\n- Browser tabs (Chrome/Safari)\n- Background sync services\n- Spotlight indexing\n- Memory pressure from too many apps\n\nLet me check processes, CPU, memory usage, and any heavy processes. I'll use top, ps, and other macOS tools to diagnose.","thinkingSignature":"a0f86a231b52c9bbc41305d2c9feb0b9d49bb692e90ed0c28c63df8a30a426aa"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me check what's running on your Mac right now! I'll pull a full diagnostic.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s64o8lrpw7xv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"top -l 3 -n 15 -r -s 2 2>&1 | grep -v \"^$\"","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s64o8lrpw7xv_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"vm_stat 1 5 2>&1 | tail -20","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s64o8lrpw7xv_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux --sort=-%cpu 2>&1 | head -25","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":44613,"output":278,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45115,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777693383464,"responseId":"0644a5ce39db21d106415a2c3d65e3e4"}}
