{"type":"message","id":"f5fbcb79","parentId":"c0480091","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:43:58.753Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me summarize:\n\n**Top CPU consumers:**\n1. **OpenClaw Gateway (node)** — PID 29665 — 82:19 CPU time, 94.4% CPU right now, 14.6% MEM (1.2GB)\n2. **WindowServer** — 14.5% CPU (normal macOS UI)\n3. **opendirectoryd** — 5.7% CPU (directory services, normal)\n4. **Telegram** — 3.7% CPU\n5. **Weather menu** — 3.6% CPU\n6. **corespotlightd** — 2.9% CPU (indexing, Spotlight)\n\n\n7. **Cursor UI View Service** — 2.0% CPU\n8. **Screen capture UI** — 1.4% CPU\n\nThe culprit is pretty obvious: OpenClaw is monopolizing the CPU with that gateway process running at 94%, consuming 1.2GB of memory. It's been running for nearly 82 minutes of CPU time since 8:55PM, which tells me it's doing some heavy work—probably related to that LLM context management with those massive SQLite shared memory files.\n\nThis is actually OpenClaw being productive rather than something malicious. That said, the MacBook Air's thermal constraints could become an issue if this keeps up.\n\nThe real take here is that OpenClaw is using about 1.2GB of RAM and maxing out the M2 CPU, which is expected for an active AI agent system. Bobby's asking if this is what's slowing down his Mac, and the answer is essentially yes—this is the trade-off for running the AI team. When idle, it should calm down, but during active processing it's going to be a resource hog.\n","thinkingSignature":"c8341ccdbbff14582ba7e5889178a1c85594fb9f5efe262d8835bf3e82d5d283"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere's the rundown Bobby:\n\n---\n\n## Your Top CPU Consumers (Right Now)\n\n| # | Process | CPU | RAM | Notes |\n|---|---------|-----|-----|-------|\n| 🔴 | **OpenClaw Gateway** | **94%** | **1.2GB** | This is ME + the whole team running |\n| 2 | WindowServer | 14% | 74MB | Normal macOS UI |\n| 3 | opendirectoryd | 6% | 7MB | Normal (directory services) |\n| 4 | Telegram | 4% | 217MB | Your Telegram app |\n| 5 | corespotlightd | 3% | 29MB | Spotlight indexing |\n| 6 | Chrome (multiple tabs) | ~2% | ~250MB | Your open tabs |\n\n---\n\n## Verdict\n\n**OpenClaw is your biggest consumer by far** — that's me, Dean, Agent X, and all the agents running.\n\n**Is that bad?** Not exactly — that's the AI team working. But on your 8GB Air, it's significant.\n\n---\n\n## What I've Been Doing Tonight\n\nWhile you've been chatting:\n- Running your Agent team\n- Setting up xurl/Agent X\n- Processing messages\n- Running the whole OpenClaw framework\n\n---\n\n## If Your Mac Feels Slow\n\n**Expected slowdowns when:**\n- I'm actively processing a complex task\n- Multiple agents are running at once\n- We're doing heavy work (research, coding, etc.)\n\n**It's fine when:**\n- Just you and me texting slowly\n- Agents are idle (not thinking)\n- Background processes are quiet\n\n---\n\n## Want Me To Ease Off?\n\nIf your Air is running hot and you need a break, I can tell the team to throttle back. But honestly Bobby — this is what you're paying for with the AI team. It's supposed to use resources when it's working.\n\n**Your call** — full speed ahead or do you need me to tell the team to pace themselves? 🛠️"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1874,"output":793,"cacheRead":54400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57067,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777693420208,"responseId":"0644a5ec2c528074df01536e0fd79b85"}}
