{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"3601\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-05-01 23:45 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"8c570b53","parentId":"df3fb759","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:45:50.326Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"c5fecd87","parentId":"8c570b53","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:46:29.622Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking about the Mac Mini benefit - essentially offloading OpenClaw to a more powerful machine so his Air can be free for other work. He's realizing that right now OpenClaw is running on his Air and consuming most of the CPU/RAM, so if he moved it to a Mac Mini, his Air would be free AND the agents could do more work simultaneously.\n\nActually wait - I need to think about this architecture more carefully. OpenClaw is the hub that runs agents. If we moved OpenClaw to a Mac Mini:\n- The Mac Mini would run the OpenClaw gateway + all agents\n- His MacBook Air would be... what exactly? A client connecting to it?\n\nOr alternatively:\n- Keep OpenClaw on the Air\n- Use Mac Mini as a worker/compute node?\n\nLet me think about how OpenClaw actually works architecturally. The OpenClaw gateway runs locally. In an ideal scenario for Bobby:\n- Mac Mini could run the heavy OpenClaw instance with all agents\n- His Air could just be the interface/control center\n- OR the Mac Mini could be dedicated to certain heavy tasks\n\nBut actually I think the simplest answer for Bobby's use case is:\n\n1. Mac Mini runs OpenClaw 24/7 (always on, fast, lots of RAM)\n2. Air connects to it as the primary interface\n3. More agents can run simultaneously without bogging down the Air\n\nThis makes sense for his vibe coder / always-on AI team lifestyle.\n","thinkingSignature":"2b21ca6fc597f83ec9a31cefe6129f22eed6929f12b31b5578f39b78e2348d74"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYES Bobby — exactly! That's the lightbulb moment. 🔦\n\n---\n\n## Right Now (MacBook Air Only)\n\n```\nMacBook Air 8GB = Everything\n- OpenClaw (me + all agents)\n- Gateway processing\n- Memory for all agents\n- Your Air is ALSO trying to run macOS + everything else\n= SLOW and TIED UP\n```\n\n---\n\n## With Mac Mini Added\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│         Mac Mini M4 Pro (24GB)          │\n│                                         │\n│   OpenClaw Hub (always on, fast)        │\n│   - Dean (coordinator)                  │\n│   - Agent X (Twitter)                   │\n│   - Cody (coding)                       │\n│   - Finn (finance)                       │\n│   - Rex (research)                      │\n│   - YoYo (YouTube)                      │\n│   - ALL agents running simultaneously   │\n│                                         │\n│   No thermal throttling!                │\n│   24GB RAM = way more headroom          │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n              ▲\n              │ lightweight connection\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│        MacBook Air (8GB)                │\n│                                         │\n│   Your interface to the team            │\n│   - Telegram chats come through here    │\n│   - Light work, you're just the boss   │\n│   - macOS runs smoothly                │\n│   - Battery friendly                   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## What This Means For You\n\n| Scenario | MacBook Air Only | Mac Mini Added |\n|----------|------------------|---------------|\n| **Agents working simultaneously** | ~2-3 before slowdown | ALL of them, all the time |\n| **Speed when team is active** | Slow, hot, fans roaring | Fast, the Mini handles it |\n| **Your Air during heavy work** | Usable but sluggish | Smooth, normal |\n| **OpenClaw uptime** | Shuts down when Air sleeps | Mac Mini runs 24/7 |\n| **Memory for agents** | 8GB shared with everything | 24GB dedicated |\n| **Doing tasks in parallel** | Agents wait in line | Agents work in parallel |\n\n---\n\n## Real Example\n\n**Right now:** You're chatting with me (Cody) + Agent X just got configured + Dean is probably idle in the background. Each agent running on your Air uses CPU/RAM. More agents = more drag.\n\n**With Mac Mini:** All agents run on the Mini, your Air is just the \"remote control.\" You could:\n- Have 10 agents all doing different tasks at once\n- Rex researching while Finn calculating while YoYo analyzing while I code — all simultaneously\n- Your Air stays cool and responsive\n\n---\n\n## The Dream Setup\n\n- **Mac Mini** → runs OpenClaw + all agents 24/7 (quiet, fast, always on)\n- **MacBook Air** → just your control interface (Telegram, messages, browser)\n\nYour Air becomes the dashboard. The Mini is the engine.\n\n---\n\n**This is why the Mac Mini recommendation made sense.** It's not about replacing your Air — it's about giving your AI team a proper home base that doesn't affect your everyday machine. 🛠️\n\nWant me to start writing up that Mac Mini setup guide we talked about earlier? I can have it ready so when you get one it's plug-and-play. 🤙"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51360,"output":1015,"cacheRead":4928,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57303,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777693550326,"responseId":"0644a673bd97fa61ce6dc0bbffbc3b0c"}}
