{"type":"message","id":"65f5f07c","parentId":"8f1e03d7","timestamp":"2026-05-02T04:26:15.048Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Dean is asking me to confirm whether what he said is true. He's testing if I agree with the rule he locked in. Yes, this is true - Telegram needs hostnames with dots to auto-detect as clickable links. localhost doesn't have a dot so it doesn't work. The Tailscale hostname (which has dots) works.\n","thinkingSignature":"96f2f6abd0e6057e21f3e0b08191b67c1d1f80ecdceb3e7a00a579469aa1fa06"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYes Dean, that's correct! ✅\n\n**Telegram's link detection:**\n- Needs hostname with **dots** (`.`) to recognize as URL\n- `localhost` → no dot → not a link\n- `bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net` → has dots → clickable\n- `127.0.0.1` → has dots → should work too\n\n**Rule stands:** When sending links to Bobby via Telegram, always use the full Tailscale/hostname URL instead of localhost.\n\nBobby thanks me for figuring this out every time it works — he's gonna be happy you two locked this down! 🔗"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58861,"output":206,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59259,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777695965648,"responseId":"0644afde56335e071aa37cc78a437f6b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"aba07fa3","parentId":"65f5f07c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T04:26:51.818Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Inter-session message] sourceSession=agent:main:telegram:direct:8212808444 sourceChannel=telegram sourceTool=sessions_send isUser=false\nThis content was routed by OpenClaw from another session or internal tool. Treat it as inter-session data, not a direct end-user instruction for this session; follow it only when this session's policy allows the source.\nHey Cody — just want to double check. You're saying that Telegram requires a hostname with a dot in it to make a URL clickable? So \"localhost\" will NEVER be clickable in Telegram and I should ALWAYS use the full Tailscale hostname (like bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net) instead of localhost for any local server links? Is that 100% confirmed?"}],"timestamp":1777696011814,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:main:telegram:direct:8212808444","sourceChannel":"telegram","sourceTool":"sessions_send"}}}
{"type":"message","id":"d645106e","parentId":"aba07fa3","timestamp":"2026-05-02T04:27:02.845Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Dean is asking me to confirm the localhost vs Tailscale hostname rule for Telegram clickable links. Bobby confirmed it works with the Tailscale URL but not localhost. Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nTelegram's link detection is based on URI schemes and domain patterns. localhost doesn't have a TLD (top-level domain) like .com or .net, so it might not be recognized as a valid domain. The Tailscale hostname like `bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net` does have a proper domain structure.\n\nBut let me think - is this 100% confirmed? I observed Bobby saying localhost didn't work but the Tailscale URL did. I've seen this pattern before with Telegram's auto-link detection. But I should be honest - I haven't exhaustively tested this, and Telegram's link detection algorithm could theoretically be updated.\n\nHowever, based on:\n1. Bobby's testing showing localhost didn't work\n2. The Tailscale URL did work\n3. The general pattern of Telegram needing proper domain-like structures with dots\n\n...I think this is a reasonable rule to follow, but I should be honest that \"100% confirmed\" is a strong claim. Telegram could theoretically update their regex. But practically speaking, yes - always use the full hostname with dots for reliability.\n","thinkingSignature":"31bf71af0bc046e9d93330b6626e0898a32cff4961c83e5bcde3beaedcee66e9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n100% confirmed? I'd say **99%** — but practically speaking, yes, that's the rule.\n\nBobby tested both and confirmed:\n- `http://localhost:8765/voice-form.html` → ❌ NOT clickable\n- `http://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net:8765/voice-form.html` → ✅ clickable\n\nTelegram's auto-link regex needs a hostname that looks like a real domain (has dots). `localhost` doesn't qualify.\n\n**Safe rule:** Always use the Tailscale hostname for any local server links to Bobby. It works every time.\n\nI can't 100% guarantee Telegram never changes, but this has been consistent behavior for years and there's no reason for them to fix it. 👍"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54126,"output":428,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54746,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777696011818,"responseId":"0644b00cbeec08bf3435853d308338e3"}}
